newsitem.title: AUSTRALIA: RTRS-No Australian Treasury note tender this week.
newsitem.headline: RTRS-No Australian Treasury note tender this week.

text.p: The Australian Treasury will not be holding a Treasury note tender this week, the Reserve Bank of Australia said.
The Treasury last week offered a total of A$1.3 billion of notes, comprising A$600 million of five-week notes, A$300 million of 13-week notes and A$400 million of 26-week notes.
There are A$441 million of non-official holdings of T-notes maturing in the week ending Oct 23.
An official for the Treasury told Reuters that the Commonwealth's projected cash position is quite healthy this week, so it did not need to undertake any short-term borrowing to fund expenditure.
